On Tue, Apr 20, 2004 at 02:23:30PM -0400, Don J wrote:
> Hi all - So far I've broken my regular big screwdriver, and my largest 
> impact spade bit trying to get this plug loose.  The plug has suffered 
> some damage as well.  The thing will not move! (even though it is 
> covered in oil :)  It's on a 1500 sp.

2 ideas for you. 

1. you are trying to turn it the correct way, right?  righty-tighty
lefty-loosie.

2. I used a file as a "lever" to help turn it. I managed to find one
that was the same thickness as the slot and put it in w/ the slot and
pulled. 

